China, Shandong, October 12, 2021 After vaccinated the second covid-vaccine for 6 months, people are eligible to get their third booster vaccination in Shandong.The precautions for novel Coronavirus vaccine booster are basically the same as those for basic immunization. Common contraindications for vaccination include:
(1) persons who are allergic to the active ingredient of the Novel Coronavirus vaccine, to any inactive ingredient of the Coronavirus vaccine, to substances used in the manufacturing process, or who have previously developed an allergy to the same type of vaccine;
(2) Those who have experienced severe allergic reactions to vaccines in the past (such as acute allergic reactions, angoneeurotic edema, dyspnea, etc.);
(3) patients with uncontrolled epilepsy and other serious neurological diseases (such as transverse myelitis, Guillain-Barre syndrome, demyelinating diseases, etc.);
(4) a person who has a fever, or is suffering from an acute disease, or an acute episode of a chronic disease, or a serious and uncontrolled chronic disease;
(5) Pregnant women.

China, Inner Mongolia; 14 May 2020. Inner Mongolia Command Centre for COVID-19 Prevention and Control: 

1. Clarifies the scope of COVID-19 testing. Testing is compulsory for
- Close contacts of the confirmed cases;
- People entering from overseas;
- People entering from medium and high-risk areas and Hubei Province;
- Fever outpatients, newly admitted patients and their companions; 
- Staff working at medical institutions; quarantine and inspection staff at ports and borders; 
- Staff working at prisons and detention houses, nursing home workers, and staff working at public venues;
- Colleges and universities staff and students who return from medium and high-risk areas.

2. Requires all local health commissions to publish a list of COVID-19 testing institutions and the telephone numbers for consultations and appointments online or via social media and update them promptly.

3. Announces that the local governments should cover the testing costs for the key populations (except for fever outpatients and newly admitted patients).

4. Requires that COVID-19 testing should be performed following the published guideline.

5. Requires all testing institutions to improve their standardised infrastructure and staff training for strengthening their testing capabilities,  improve their laboratory safety management, and record and archive staff details.

China, Inner Mongolia; 14 May 2020. Inner Mongolia Command Centre for COVID-19 Prevention and Control clarifies the scope of COVID-19 testing. Testing is voluntary for those who are NOT: 

- Close contacts of confirmed case;
- Entering from overseas;
- Entering from medium or high-risk areas or from Hubei Province;
- Fever outpatients, newly admitted patients or their companions; 
- Working at medical institutions; quarantine and inspection staff working at ports and borders; 
- Working at prisons and detention houses, nursing homes, or public venues; or
- Colleges or universities staff or students who return from medium or high-risk areas.
